                     <interp inst="t18220109-87-person832" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220109-87-person832" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . My brother is a <rs id="t18220109-87-viclabel450" type="occupation">butcher</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220109-87-victim831 t18220109-87-viclabel450"></join>, and lives in Union-street, Spitalfields. On the 8th of December between six and seven o'clock in the evening; I was watching his shop, and saw the prisoner pass the door, and take two breasts of mutton off the stall board, wrap it in a cloth, and walk away - I took him.</p>
               <p>WM. MILLER. Having been frequently robbed, I set my brother to watch - he brought the prisoner, who said another boy took it and gave it him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I picked it of the ground.</p>
               <p>
